How to avoid becoming a second Wuhan

It is the common proposition of other cities in Hubei in the current anti-epidemic

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 29, officers and soldiers of the Huanggang detachment of the Chinese People's armed police fought to transport supplies to Dabie Mountains's regional medical center, which was tasked with quarantine duties. Photo / Xinhua

Wuhan isn't the only place: Hubei Province in crisis

Staff Writer / Tian Xu, Angie Pao, hosiey hosiey

PUBLISHED: February 17,2020

On January 21, Huanggang became the first city outside Wuhan to report a confirmed case. On January 27, following the first notification of a confirmed case by the Shennongjia, 12 prefecture level cities, one autonomous prefecture and four provincial level county level administrative units in Hubei Province all reported confirmed cases.

On January 23rd cities across Hubei Province published lists of designated hospitals. On that day, Wuhan "closed city" , Ezhou, Huanggang and other cities close behind, in addition to the mountains and forests of Shennongjia outside, all cities in Hubei have entered the "closed city" state.

"An emergency in Huanggang, " "an emergency in Xiaogan, " "an emergency in Ezhou, " "an emergency in Suizhou, " "an emergency in Tianmen, " ... as the number of confirmed cases continues to climb, beds are scarce, medical personnel are in short supply, and supplies are unsustainable, similar stories have appeared in the media in turn.

In contrast to Wuhan, which has the medical resources of dozens of top three hospitals, the rest of Hubei has the largest number of top four general hospitals, such as Yichang, according to China News Weekly, huanggang, Xiaogan, Suizhou, Ezhou, Yellowstone, Xianning; some don't even have any, like Shennongjia.

"Huanggang must not be allowed to become a second Wuhan, " Xiaodong Wang, Hubei's governor, said at a news conference on Jan. 29, referring to other cities such as Xiaogan.

How to avoid becoming a second Wuhan is a common proposition for other cities in Hubei in the fight against the epidemic.

The ever-increasing number of confirmed cases

Xiaogan and Huanggang, with their extremely high numbers of confirmed cases, are the most prominent cities in the province, with the exception of Wuhan. As of 2400 hours on February 10, Xiaogan had 2,642 confirmed cases and Huanggang had 2,332, double the number of Suizhou (1,095) .

Huanggang and Xiaogan, the two closest cities in the province geographically to and from Wuhan, are both inside the one-hour high-speed rail ring. As the province's second-most-registered residents (Huanggang, 7.406 m) and fifth-most-registered residents (Xiaogan, 5.175 m) , its huge population base and convenient transportation all predestined the number of people coming and going to Wuhan.

According to big data from Baidu, Huanggang and Xiaogan are the two most important destinations for Wuhan's migrant population between January 16 and 22, the peak of the Lunar New Year travel season, and more than 25 percent of migrants from Wuhan are admitted each day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Before Wuhan imposed traffic controls, 14 percent of those leaving the city reached Huanggang, or about 700,000 people, said Chen Shaomin, deputy mayor of Huanggang. According to Xiaogan Mayor Wu Haitao, of the 5.06 million people in Xiaogan in the first round, 393,500 returned from Wuhan. A total of 11,524 people were found to have fever, of whom 4509 returned home from Wuhan. As of January 31,60 percent of the confirmed cases and 66 percent of the suspected cases were in Wuhan.

Several other cities in Hubei Province with the highest number of confirmed cases, including Jingzhou, Xiangyang, Suizhou, Huangshi and Yichang, were also among the cities with the closest ties to Wuhan the week before the closure, according to Baidu big data.

In recent days, the number of confirmed cases has drawn attention in two other cities, Ezhou and Suizhou, which have the smallest populations among the prefectural-level cities in Hubei. As of 2400 on February 10, the cumulative number of confirmed cases in these two cities had reached 790 and 1,095 respectively, the latter has jumped to fourth place in Hubei.

Ezhou is located between Huanggang and Wuhan, a small area, but Wuhan is very closely linked, less than half an hour from the inter-city railway to Wuhan, in the words of the locals, "to buy a house in Wuhan, in Wuhan Employment. ". Suizhou is a little further away, but as an agricultural city, there are many people working in Wuhan. About 80 percent of the 112,000 people who returned to Suizhou from Wuhan before the holiday came from the countryside, said Ke Ke, the mayor of Suizhou.

Also of note is the change in the number of new diagnoses. This data is not only related to the number of infections, population base, but also related to changes in nucleic acid detection capacity, Huanggang, filial piety data can illustrate this issue.

NUCLEIC ACID testing has been a major concern in cities throughout Hubei Province from the closure of the city to the beginning of February. Among the suggestions given by the central inspection team sent to Huanggang is to improve the inspection scheme, optimize the inspection process and speed up the inspection.

Until January 16th, nucleic acid testing is at the National Center for Disease Control. Since then, the state has delegated the power of testing to the Hubei Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention, with a detection capacity of about 300 cases per day. After January 20, the city has the right to test, but the first test results sent to the province for review. This led to Huanggang's first notification of a confirmed case on January 22 and Xiaogan's first notification of a confirmed case on January 24.

At first, the supply of kits is not sufficient, the city's hospitals are more cautious in sending tests. Li Ling (not his real name) , the head nurse of a township hospital in Huanggang, told China News weekly that the hospital checked the temperature of the patient, then took blood samples, throat swabs and a CT scan of the chest. Suspected cases were admitted, one Room each to avoid cross-contamination. If fever persists within three days after observation, the patient shall be referred to the District People's Hospital for consultation. If the patient is considered as a suspected case, the patient shall be sent to the district people's Hospital for further diagnosis and other steps. More often than not, the township hospital has had more than a dozen suspected cases.

Later, the supply of reagent kits in various cities gradually sufficient, but limited to testing manpower shortage, testing speed is still not fast. Huanggang, Xiaogan have also been public appeal, the need to enrich the testing staff.

The change in Huanggang began on January 29, when the Macheng and Xishui County counties were allowed to test and the number of confirmed cases rose. Over the next few days, eight staff from the CDC, five from the Wuhan Institute of Virology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and four from the Yunnan Center for Disease Control and Prevention arrived at their posts one by one to beef up laboratory testing staff at the Huanggang Center for Disease Control and Prevention, to speed up the delivery of suspected cases.

The number of confirmed cases has increased rapidly in a short period of time. At the time, Huanggang's mayor, Qiu Lixin, said that by February 2, more than 1,000 suspected cases in Huanggang would soon be detected, and that a large proportion of them could be confirmed, so there's GonNa be a big increase in confirmed cases in Huanggang in the next two days. Indeed, February 1 and 2 are the two new Huanggang peaks for the day to date, 276 and 244 respectively.

Xiaogan also welcomed four support staff from the CDC on January 31, and the number of confirmed cases has risen since then.

Yang Yunyan, vice governor of Hubei Province, provided a set of data, at that time, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention had a total of 83 laboratory inspectors supporting Hubei. On February 5, the province tested 12,277 samples and 6,500 samples from Wuhan.

It was from that day that the cumulative rankings of confirmed cases in Huanggang and Xiaogan changed. As of 2400 hours that day, the number of confirmed cases in Xiaogan surpassed that in Huanggang for the first time, making it the second most populous city in the province and even the whole country, with 424 new cases, bringing the total to 1,886, and 162 new cases, bringing the total to 1,807, in Huanggang.

Dai Jiequn, deputy director of Xiaogan's Health Commission, said in an interview that this was mainly due to Xiaogan's focus on sampling, sending tests and confirming diagnoses, with a total of 2,155 samples sent in the past two days, the samples were taken from patients who had been monitored in isolation at fever clinics, and from suspected patients who had been treated in isolation but had not been tested in time because the tests failed to keep up.

Xiaogan Yunmeng County People's Hospital General Party Branch Secretary Liu Houhui also confirmed this statement. Recently, the Yunmeng County People's hospital will be suspected of cases of samples were handed over for testing.

From February 1 to 6,5,668 samples were sent to Xiaogan, 1.83 times the previous total, Xiaogan Mayor Wu Haitao told reporters. So far, Xiaogan has basically completed the cumulative screening of suspected cases. In addition, all fever outpatient admission and admission of suspected cases are included in the test object. Among them, 3708 samples were collected from the observation staff of fever clinic, which shortened the time of diagnosis for a large number of real patients.

Bed Expansion, as fast as you can

With the number of confirmed and suspected cases rising, the first question is, are there enough beds? Cities with weaker Base and more people diagnosed face greater pressure on the issue, such as Huanggang.

Huanggang Mayor Qiu Lixin made public the number of beds in Huanggang at a press conference on Feb. 1. The city's 29 designated hospitals have a total capacity of 4,200 beds and 2,831 rooms. From initial public confirmations to the present, Huanggang has undergone several rounds of bed expansion, from urban to rural areas.

On January 21, the day after the announcement in Zhong Nanshan that new pneumonia could be transmitted from person to person, 13 designated hospitals and 29 fever clinics were identified in Huanggang. There are three designated hospitals in the city, namely City Infectious Disease Hospital, Huimin Hospital and Longwangshan elderly apartment, with a total of 360 beds.

Three days later, with cases mounting rapidly, Huanggang decided to fire off the unfinished Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center, called the Dabie Mountains Medical Center, or Florida, a new wing of the Huanggang City Center Hospital, it was supposed to move in May. The Huanggang version of Little Tangshan offers more than 1,000 extra beds.

According to media reports, the county and township hospitals assume the function of collecting the bottom due to the graded diagnosis and treatment system. Li Ling (not his real name) , the head nurse of a township hospital in Huanggang, told China Newsweek on January 24 that the hospital had converted several floors of the Medical Department into isolation wards. There have been media reports that the "fever ward" set up by the hospital of the town of Liuhe in Qichun County, Huanggang City, on January 31 was an 8-container set up in a 1,200-square-meter board room in a driving school, the town's "Little Tangshan" can accommodate 40 patients.

In case of emergency, does the bed and ward meet the standard of "infectious ward" ? The answer is no.

Liu Jun, deputy director of the Intensive Care Unit at Hengyang Central Hospital and leader of the medical team in Hengyang, told China News weekly that Huimin County Hospital in downtown Huanggang is a community hospital, can Not afford the rescue and treatment of critically ill patients. After becoming fixed-point hospital, transforms the isolation area temporarily, increases the bed.

Same thing at the Huanggang Infectious Disease Hospital. Sun Liang (not his real name) told China Newsweek that after his father was diagnosed, he repeatedly begged doctors for a fever clinic and was finally admitted to the city's Infectious Disease Hospital. Sun Liang was told by his father that the hospital was in poor condition. At this time the condition has been more serious, he can not even monitor the blood oxygen all day. Two days after checking in, my father died. Sun Liang's last call was to take a sip of hot porridge the next morning -- as if the hospital had a tiny microwave and he couldn't get out of bed to heat it.

The Third Designated Hospital in downtown Huanggang is not even a hospital, just an old-age apartment that has been temporarily set up as a quarantine zone for suspected patients.

Even the Dabie Mountains Medical Center, known as Huanggang's version of Little Tangshan, was rudimentary when the Hengyang medical team arrived. Waterproof floors, beds and simple isolation are available, but the centre itself is not built to the specifications of an Infectious Disease Hospital. It is a temporary renovation, with nurses'stations and doctors'stations connected to wards. Infectious Disease Wards require clear lines of access for patients and health care workers, as well as contaminated areas and buffer zones to ensure the source of infection is cut off, which are not available at Dabie Mountains medical centres. Liu Jun and others temporarily made a simple division of these passageways with plastic boards, wooden boards, etc. , and still rely more on personal protection.

The rapid increase in cases did not give the cities of Hubei time to build specialized wards.

On January 22, the Department of Infectious Diseases was vacated in the Tuan Cheng Shan Hospital area of Huangshi Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine for the treatment of confirmed cases. Five days later, all the hospital areas were vacated, as a whole, for the treatment of confirmed COVID-19 pneumonia patients. On January 29, leishan hospital was built in Ezhou on the basis of the old hospital district. It is designed with 386 rooms and 772 beds in the form of "container + Movable Board Room" . It is expected to be delivered on February 15, the new Shiyan Crown Pneumonia second-aid hospital has opened with three wards with a capacity of 100 beds

Yang Yunyan, the vice governor of Hubei Province, said that as of 2400 hours on January 31,120 designated hospitals had been established outside Wuhan in Hubei Province, strengthening the requisition and renovation of existing hospital beds, and at the same time requiring all localities to follow the principles of scientific treatment and quick response, through the reconstruction, expansion of existing medical institutions to focus on new treatment hospitals, or in the form of requisitioning hotels, hotels and other forms to speed up the increase in treatment places.

Since the spread of NCP, the prevention of cross-infection in three areas of infectious wards (clean, contaminated and semi-contaminated areas) and two channels (medical staff and patient channels) have been barely achieved in many of the temporary vacated wards.

In addition to admitted patients, suspected cases, fever patients who can not be ruled out of infection and close contacts of confirmed patients are also of concern. This group is the focus of prevention and control, if not well controlled, they will become a "mobile source of infection. ".

On February 2, Wuhan proposed to centralise treatment and quarantine for these categories of people, and the province then formally issued the request to municipalities.

As of February 9, there were 142 fever patients in Xiaogan with 5,111 rooms, mainly in hotels, schools and other places, Xiaogan Health Commission told the media.

Liu Houhui told China News weekly that as a second-class hospital, many of its departments have been closed, and wards have been vacated to accommodate suspected patients, "The main part of the hospital is basically for fever patients, other treatment can be put back to put back. "

Liu Jun, director of China Merchants Yunmeng County, told China News weekly that Yunmeng County had requisitioned 17 hotels to watch for close contacts of fever patients and confirmed patients. China merchants was in charge of one of the hotels, keeping watch for more than 40 close contacts, one for each of you. If one of them is found to have a fever, he is immediately taken to a fever clinic.

Emergency call for medical volunteers

Li Lanjuan, a member of the high-level Expert Group of the National Health Commission, said in an interview that under this epidemic, many doctors serve several patients in other parts of the country, while in Hubei, one doctor has to take care of many patients, so the medical staff is very hard, medical resources shortage and other problems are also shown.

In terms of the resident population, there are 1,000 medical practitioners per 1,000 people in cities across Hubei. Apart from Jingzhou and Qianjiang, which did not release specific figures in their 2018 bulletins, the most anxious are Suizhou and Xiaogan, with 1.83 and 1.89 respectively, in addition, Tianmen, Huanggang and Ezhou are all about 2 people, and Wuhan is about 3.45 people.

In absolute terms, excluding the special circumstances of several county-level cities, there are fewer than 10,000 practitioners in Ezhou, Suizhou, Huangshi, Jingmen, Ensch and Xiaogan, and 38,200 in Wuhan. It is not difficult to imagine that the constant increase in the number of confirmed and suspected cases in various cities has brought great pressure to the medical staff.

Around January 25, each province selected by inhalation medicine, infectious diseases, critical medical science composed of medical teams rushed to all cities in Hubei, to reinforce the local medical forces.

However, several municipalities have since sent out calls for help.

On January 27th Huanggang's defence and Control Command took the lead in calling for state support and mobilising personnel. Because of the great clinical demand in Huanggang and the weak medical treatment force, although there are two medical teams in Hunan and Shandong to reinforce, but the rescue force is concentrated at the city level, county and township level medical personnel, testing technology personnel is still seriously inadequate. Urgent Need Epidemiology expert 6 people, examination examination expert 4 people, aspiration, serious disease, infection professional doctor 523 people, nursing staff 911 people.

On February 6th Suizhou, too, called for 718 people, including 212 Doctors and 506 nurses, to be evacuated.

On the same day, Yang Yunyan, vice governor of Hubei Province, also mentioned that there is still a shortage of medical personnel at present, and nine cities and states have requested support for medical personnel. The gap is estimated to be around 2,250, and this is a conservative figure.

Another way to ask for help is to ask for volunteers.

On February 3, the Xiangyang Prevention and Control Command made a public announcement to recruit medical volunteers. Within a day and a half, 603 people signed up, and 326 qualified people were initially vetted. A few days later, 46 volunteers took up their posts.

At the same time, Ezhou, which ranks high in terms of infection rate and case fatality rate, has launched an initiative in the hope that under 60 years of age (which may be relaxed depending on the physical condition) , healthy retired and retired medical workers and individual medical workers actively participated in the prevention and control of the epidemic. A few days later, 97 people signed up, and volunteers are already on the job.

In the message, it is worth noting that both Huanggang and Suizhou have mentioned the need for doctors such as "critical care medicine, infectious diseases, and respiratory medicine, " who can be said to be essential to the treatment of severe illnesses, especially those in critical condition, everywhere, to some extent, the case fatality rate is also related.

Suizhou has said publicly at the press conference that it will in principle focus on the treatment of critically ill patients in confirmed cases at its central hospitals to do its utmost to reduce the case fatality rate.

Suizhou has asked for medical assistance. On February 5, a 31-member medical team from the provincial cancer hospital was sent to Suizhou overnight. Zhu Dingcheng, the team leader, told China Newsweek that the SUIZHOU's request for support from the Department of Critical Care Medicine had already resulted in 834 confirmed cases and nine deaths in Suizhou.

The 31-member support team comprises 10 doctors and 6 nurses from the intensive care unit as well as 15 nurses from other general wards. Among them, 10 medical experts in four groups entered the Intensive Care Unit and Infectious Diseases Unit 1, Unit 2 and Unit 4 of Suizhou Central Hospital respectively to participate in the unit duty to guide and help treat critically ill patients. There are currently 32 critically ill patients and 33 critically ill patients in Suizhou.

Currently, the mortality rate in Hubei Province is the most interesting city, in addition to Wuhan is Tianmen. As of 2400 hours on February 10,261 cases had been confirmed and 10 deaths had been recorded in Tianmen. The case fatality rate of 3.83% was lower than that of 4.05% in Wuhan and higher than that of other cities.

The 10 deaths occurred between January 27 and February 2, the Tianmen COVID-19 Pneumonia Control Command told China Newsweek. Among them, 5 cases died on the second day of admission and 5 cases died with other underlying diseases.

On February 8, the national expert group went to Tianmen to guide the rescue work, including Tu Yuanchao, a party member and deputy director of the provincial health and Health Commission, Director of the Chinese Society of Critical Care Medicine and director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine of the first hospital affiliated to the National Sun Yat-sen University, Guan Xiangdong, jiang Rongmeng, chief physician of the Second Department of infection, Temple of Earth Hospital, Beijing.

According to the prevention and Control Command, at that time, the expert group believed that 5 cases died on the second day of admission and lost the opportunity for early treatment, so it emphasized timely medical treatment; 5 cases died of complications of basic diseases such as uremia and diabetes, therefore, it is emphasized that multi-disciplinary cooperation should be strengthened, related specialties should be rationally integrated, and "one person, one policy" should be realized. In addition, there are many factors contributing to the high mortality rate of Tianmen. For example, the low number of confirmed positive cases of nucleic acid testing is one of the reasons, which does not conform to the regular pattern of positive rates in the whole province, the causes should be carefully analyzed and improved from the aspects of Specimen Collection Standard, laboratory quality control and so on.

Perhaps as a result, 44 new cases were confirmed in Tianmen on February 10, double the previous one-day increase. As of 2400 hours on 10 February, there were still 96 severe cases and three critical cases in Tianmen, representing 41.4 per cent of the 239 patients currently under treatment.

On February 7, Guo Yanhong, commissioner of the medical and Health Bureau of the National Health Commission, said at a press conference that the 16 provinces would establish a counterpart support relationship to support cities outside Wuhan and give full support to Hubei Province in strengthening patient care.

At present, this group of support medical staff is one by one in place phase, after all the cure rate and mortality rate remains to be seen.

"where's the mask? "

"We have zero N95[ masks ] , Zero Hazmat inventory on our charity's side! "

On the afternoon of February 8, the Xiaogan General Committee of charities gave an interview to the media and asked for urgent help for medical supplies. Since around January 25, hospitals in cities other than Wuhan turned to the community for help, hoping that people from all walks of life would rush to help with medical supplies such as rapid test kits, temperature guns, medical N95 masks, medical masks, goggles, protective clothing, disinfectant, etc. , similar requests for help have been repeated over and over, and have not improved. In Xiaogan, Huanggang, where the largest number of people have been diagnosed, the discrepancy is striking.

When Liu Jun's team from Hengyang, Hunan Province, arrived at the Dabie Mountains Medical Center, supplies were tight. They are usually organized into groups that enter the contaminated area on the basis of meeting the minimum number of medical personnel. When the supply is really bad, then to the Dabie Mountains Medical Center to urge the relevant leadership.

The same is true of the Dabie Mountains Medical Center, and even more so of the hospitals in the cities, counties and towns. At the end of December, when the news of pneumonia first came out, the hospital purchased several batches of N95 masks for medical use, Cheung Chi-kong, head of medical supplies purchasing at Huangzhou General Hospital in Huanggang City, told China Newsweek. The last purchase was before the Spring Festival, when the supply was extremely tight, 30,000 masks from Shaanxi, the price rose from 4.5 yuan to 9.5 yuan each.

Cheung Chi-kong said he was being asked for a mask every day, "But I really can't help it. Sometimes when I'm in a hurry, I let people take five or 10 key departments and assign them to themselves. Now when you go to these hospitals, none of the doctors and nurses in the general departments wear N95. "

Hospitals can only give priority to fever clinics, infectious diseases and CT rooms, which are the most at risk. Other departments have taken the next step, securing surgical masks, medical care masks or industrial-standard masks.

Liu Houhui has the same anxiety. Similar to the HUANGZHOU General Hospital, the Yunmeng County People's Hospital of Xiaogan City can only supply medical N95 masks to the isolation ward, the Department of infection and other departments with the greatest risk, and all other departments are ordinary masks, hospital leaders are no exception.

Before the Spring Festival, Yunmeng County People's Hospital purchased dozens of medical N95 masks, dozens of sets of medical protective clothing. According to past experience, there is a two-year shelf life of protective clothing are usually not used, the end is usually reported damaged.

This is the normal situation in district, county and township hospitals, limited by the financial chain, coupled with these years also very few infectious diseases, medical protective clothing, medical N95 masks are not available. At the beginning of the epidemic, if the grass-roots hospital can have a hundred sets of protective clothing inventory, even if a lot of.

On the night of January 28, the hospital was about to run out of N95 masks for medical use. After coordination, they urgently sent a car to Wuhan to bring back more than 500 masks donated by others.

One interviewee, who did not want to be named, said that even if there was good material distributed by the higher authorities, it was rarely given to the county level. In the face of difficulties, the local approach to almost a few: purchase, waiting for a direct donation and higher-level transfer.

Around the Chinese New Year, the Yunmeng County government set up a material support group. Liu Jun, director of the China Merchants Bureau, became a non-staff member. He was responsible for developing material channels and casting a wide net together with the Economic Information Bureau, the Federation of Industry and Commerce and the Bureau of Commerce, as he had extensive contacts with the outside world.

Before the epidemic, the hospital's material purchase must pass through the province unified purchase platform, the platform has one round of sifting to the related enterprise, the hospital selects, negotiates the price in this scope, through the hospital related department person in charge to discuss together, finally signs the contract. Generally speaking, the contract with the hospital is usually the dealer, few manufacturers directly to sign.

After the outbreak, buyers usually have to leave the intermediate procurement platform, find dealers, manufacturers. The two sides may have never dealt with each other, and there is no credible intermediate platform, so the crisis of confidence arises. Yunmeng County usually chooses a fellow countryman as an intermediary guarantor, to contact the source or channel. For example, a fellow countryman in another province asked his friend to buy 20,000 masks in Dubai, fly them back to Shanghai and then Hubei.

There are also private volunteer organizations that take on the role of entrustment purchase in this process. Volunteer Guo Fei is a Xiaogan who started his own business in Shenzhen. He set up a group on New Year's Eve. More volunteers joined the group to form several groups, such as material development, Material follow-up, logistics guarantee, financial disclosure and procurement group entrusted by the organization. Gradually, including Xiaogan City Center Hospital (3A) , including more than 60 Xiaogan City, district and county hospitals and township hospitals have gradually joined. The hospital, the civilian volunteer, the official has formed this "the Medical Demand Union" together.

In the course of purchasing, several parties found that many manufacturers of protective equipment had gradually been taken over by the local government and could not sell to the cities of Hubei, and there were signs of localism in some places. Guo Fei said that a batch of gloves from Nanchang Jinxian County, Jiangxi Province, the driver went to pick up the goods with various certificates with red stamps issued by the epidemic prevention headquarters, but was stopped at the county border. One day and night later, after Xiaogan and other districts and counties and local coordination and communication, the goods were released. They have also contacted Anhui Alcohol Factory, but the other has been taken over, not for sale, "we have no factory, only by buying. You do not sell, I do? "

As of February 4, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology had coordinated domestic production enterprises to send 219,000 pieces of medical protective clothing and 233,000 pairs of goggles to Hubei; as of February 7, the number of mask production enterprises in China had reached 73 percent, said Capacity utilization, a spokesman for the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, the Capacity utilization rate for medical masks has reached 87 percent.

But in recent days, many hospitals around the city is still constantly sending out messages to the outside world, masks, protective clothing, isolation clothing, alcohol and so on are still in a tight balance. "where did the materials go? " More than one interviewee raised the question, but still has not been answered.
